<plot>The life and work of the great and equally controversial American poet (1885-1872) runs through the most violent and crucial period of the 20th century and sheds light on modern-day Europe in a way we cannot ignore. The commentary is by Andonis Zervas, who translated The Pisan Cantos into Greek.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?186772</url></doc>
